1010101.Message:
To conform to Version 1 of the Hierarchical Model Composition package specification for SBML Level 3, an SBML document must declare the use of the following XML Namespace: 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/comp/version1'
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.1
1010101.ShortMessage: The comp ns is not correctly declared

1010102.Message:
Wherever they appear in an SBML document, elements and attributes from the Hierarchical Model Composition package must be declared either implicitly or explicitly to be in the XML namespace 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/comp/version1'
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.1

1010301.Message:
(Extends validation rule #10301 in the SBML Level 3 Version 1 Core specification.) Within a <model> or <modelDefinition> object, the values of the attributes id and comp:id on every instance of the following classes of objects must be unique across the set of all id and comp:id attribute values of all such objects in a model: the model itself, plus all contained <functionDefinition>, <compartment>, <species>, <reaction>, <speciesReference>, <modifierSpeciesReference>, <event>, and <parameter> objects, plus the <submodel> and <deletion> objects defined by the Hierarchical Model Composition package, plus any objects defined by any other package with 'package:id' attributes defined as falling in the 'SId' namespace.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.9

1010302.Message:
The values of the attributes 'id' and 'comp:id' on every instance of all <model>, <modelDefinition>, and <externalModelDefinition> objects must be unique across the set of all 'id' and 'comp:id' attribute values of such objects in the SBML document to which they belong.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.9
1010302.ShortMessage: Model and ExternalModelDefinitions must have unique ids

1010303.Message:
Within <model> and <modelDefinition> objects inside an SBML document, the value of the attribute 'comp:id' on every instance of a <port> object must be unique across the set of all 'comp:id' attribute values of all such objects in the model.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.9

1010304.Message:
The value of a comp:id attribute must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 3.1.7

1010308.Message:
The value of a 'comp:submodelRef' attribute on <replacedElement> and <replacedBy> objects must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2

1010309.Message:
The value of a 'comp:deletion' attribute on <replacedElement> objects must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2

1010310.Message:
The value of a 'comp:conversionFactor' attribute on <replacedElement> objects must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2

1010311.Message:
The value of a 'comp:name' attribute must always conform to the syntax of type string.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 3.1.1

1010501.Message:
If one element replaces another, whether it is the target of a <replacedBy> element, or whether it has a child <replacedElement>, the units of the replaced element, multiplied by the units of any applicable conversion factor, should equal the units of the replacement element.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.5
1010501.ShortMessage: Units of replaced elements should match replacement units.

1020101.Message:
Any object derived from the extended SBase class (defined in the Hierarchical Model Composition package) may contain at most one instance of a <listOfReplacedElements> subobject.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6

1020102.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfReplacedElements> container object may only contain <replacedElement> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6

1020103.Message:
A <listOfReplacedElements> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <listOfReplacedElements> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6

1020104.Message:
The <listOfReplacedElements> in an SBase object is optional, but if present, must not be empty.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6

1020105.Message:
Any object derived from the extended SBase class (defined in the Hierarchical Model Composition package) may contain at most one instance of a <replacedBy> subobject.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6

1020201.Message:
In all SBML documents using the HierarchicalModel Composition package, the SBML object must include a value for the attribute 'comp:required' attribute.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 4.1.2

1020202.Message:
The value of attribute 'comp:required' on the SBML object must be of the data type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 4.1.2
1020202.ShortMessage: The comp:required attribute must be Boolean

1020203.Message:
The value of attribute 'comp:required' on the SBML object must be set to 'true' if the Model object within the SBML object contains any Submodel with Species, Parameter, Compartment, Reaction, or Event objects that have not been either directly or indirectly replaced.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.1
1020203.ShortMessage: The comp:required attribute must be 'true' if math changes

1020204.Message:
The value of attribute 'comp:required' on the SBML object must be set to 'false' if the Model object within the SBML object contains no Submodel objects, or if all Submodel objects that are present contain no Species, Parameter, Compartment, Reaction, or Event objects that have not been either directly or indirectly replaced.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.1
1020204.ShortMessage: The comp:required attribute must be 'false' if math does not change

1020205.Message:
There may be at most one instance of the <listOfModelDefinitions> within an SBML object that uses the SBML Level 3 Hierarchical Model Composition package.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3

1020206.Message:
The various 'ListOf' subobjects within an SBML object are optional, but if present, these container objects must not be empty. Specifically, if any of the following classes of objects is present within the SBML object, it must not be empty: <listOfModelDefinitions> and <listOfExternalModelDefinitions>.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3

1020207.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfModelDefinitions> container may only contain <modelDefinition> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3

1020208.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfExternalModelDefinitions> container may only contain <externalModelDefinition> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3

1020209.Message:
A <listOfModelDefinitions> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <listOfModelDefinitions> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3

1020210.Message:
A <listOfExternalModelDefinitions> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <listOfExternalModelDefinitions> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3

1020211.Message:
There may be at most one instance of the <listOfExternalModelDefinitions> within an SBML object that uses the SBML Level 3 Hierarchical Model Composition package.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3

1020212.Message:
The value of attribute 'comp:required' on the SBML object must be set to 'true'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.1

1020301.Message:
An <externalModelDefinition> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an <externalModelDefinition> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.2

1020302.Message:
An <externalModelDefinition> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotation.  No other subobjects from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Hierarchical Model Composition namespace are permitted on an <externalModelDefinition> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3.2

1020303.Message:
An <externalModelDefinition> object must have the attributes 'comp:id' and 'comp:source', and may have the optional attributes 'comp:name', 'comp:modelRef', and 'comp:md5'. No other attributes from the Hierarchical Model Composition namespace are permitted on an <externalModelDefinition> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3.2

1020304.Message:
The value of the 'comp:source' attribute on an <externalModelDefinition> object must reference an SBML Level 3 document.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3.2

1020305.Message:
The value of the 'comp:modelRef' attribute on an <externalModelDefinition> object must be the value of an id attribute on a <model>, <modelDefinition>, or <externalModelDefinition> object in the SBML document referenced by the 'comp:source' attribute.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3.2
1020305.ShortMessage: 'modelRef' must be the 'id' of a model in the 'source' document

1020306.Message:
The value of the 'comp:md5' attribute, if present on an <externalModelDefinition> object, should match the calculated MD5 checksum of the SBML document referenced by the 'comp:source' attribute. 
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3.2
1020306.ShortMessage: MD5 checksum does not match the 'source' document

1020307.Message:
The value of a 'comp:source' attribute on an <externalModelDefinition> object must always conform to the syntax of the XML Schema 1.0 data type 'anyURI'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3.2
1020307.ShortMessage: The 'comp:source' attribute must be of type 'anyURI'

1020308.Message:
The value of a comp:modelRef attribute on an <externalModelDefinition> object must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3.2
1020308.ShortMessage: The 'comp:modelRef' attribute must have the syntax of 'SId'

1020309.Message:
The value of a comp:md5 attribute on an <externalModelDefinition> object must always conform to the syntax of type string.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3.2
1020309.ShortMessage: The 'comp:md5' attribute must have the syntax of 'string'

1020310.Message:
An <externalModelDefinition> object must not reference an <externalModelDefinition> in a different SBML document that, in turn, refers back to the original <externalModelDefinition object, whether directly or indirectly through a chain of <externalModelDefinition> objects. 
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3.2

1020501.Message:
There may be at most one instance of each of the following kinds of objects within a <model> or <modelDefinition> object using Hierarchical Model Composition: <listOfSubmodels> and <listOfPorts>.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4

1020502.Message:
The various ListOf subobjects with a <model> object are optional, but if present, these container object must not be empty.  Specifically, if any of the following classes of objects are present on the <model>, it must not be empty: <listOfSubmodels> and <listOfPorts>.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4

1020503.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfSubmodels> container object may only contain <submodel> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4

1020504.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfPorts> container object may only contain <port> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4

1020505.Message:
A <listOfSubmodels> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <listOfSubmodels> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4

1020506.Message:
A <listOfPorts> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <listOfPorts> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4

1020601.Message:
A <submodel> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <submodel> object.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 3.2

1020602.Message:
A <submodel> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations.  No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <submodel> object.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 3.2

1020603.Message:
There may be at most one <listOfDeletions> container object within a <submodel> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5

1020604.Message:
A <listOfDeletions> container object within a <submodel> object is optional, but if present, must not be empty.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5

1020605.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfDeletions> container object may only contain <deletion> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5

1020606.Message:
A <listOfDeletions> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <listOfReplacedElements> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5

1020607.Message:
A <submodel> object must have the attributes 'comp:id' and 'comp:modelRef' because they are required, and may also have the optional attributes 'comp:name', 'comp:timeConversionFactor, and/or 'comp:extentConversionFactor'.  No other attributes from the Hierarchical Model Composition namespace are permitted on a <submodel> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5

1020608.Message:
The value of a 'comp:modelRef' attribute on a <submodel> object must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId. 
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.1

1020613.Message:
The value of a 'comp:timeConversionFactor' attribute on a <submodel> object must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId. 
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.1

1020614.Message:
The value of a 'comp:extentConversionFactor' attribute on a <submodel> object must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId. 
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.1

1020615.Message:
The value of a 'comp:modelRef' attribute on a <submodel> must be the identifier of a <model>, <modelDefinition>, or <externalModelDefinition> object in the same SBML object as the <submodel>.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.1
1020615.ShortMessage: The 'comp:modelRef' attribute must reference a model

1020616.Message:
A <model> or <modelDefinition> object must not contain a <submodel> which references that model object itself. That is, the value of a 'comp:modelRef' attribute on a <submodel> must not be the value of the parent <model> or <modelDefinition>'s 'id' attribute.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.1
1020616.ShortMessage: The 'comp:modelRef' attribute cannot reference own model

1020617.Message:
A <model> object must not contain a <submodel> which references that <model> indirectly. That is, the 'comp:modelRef' attribute of a <submodel> may not point to the 'id' of a <model> containing a <submodel> object that references the original <model> directly or indirectly through a chain of <model>/<submodel> pairs.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.1
1020617.ShortMessage: <model> may not reference <submodel> that references itself.

1020622.Message:
The value of a 'comp:timeConversionFactor' attribute on a given <submodel> object must be the identifier of a <parameter> object defined in the same Model containing the <submodel>.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.1

1020623.Message:
The value of a 'comp:extentConversionFactor' attribute on a given <submodel> object must be the identifier of a <parameter> object defined in the same Model containing the <submodel>.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.1

1020701.Message:
The value of a 'comp:portRef' attribute on an <sBaseRef> object must be the identifier of a <port> object in the <model> referenced by that <sBaseRef>.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020701.ShortMessage: The 'comp:portRef' attribute must be the 'id' of a <port>

1020702.Message:
The value of a 'comp:idRef' attribute on an <sBaseRef> object must be the identifier of an object contained in (that is, within the SId namespace of) the <model> referenced by that <sBaseRef>. This includes objects with 'id' attributes defined in packages other than SBML Level 3 Core or the Hierarchical Model Composition package.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020702.ShortMessage: The 'comp:idRef' attribute must be the 'id' of a model element

1020703.Message:
The value of a 'comp:unitRef' attribute on an <sBaseRef> object must be the identifier of a <unitDefinition< object contained in the <model> referenced by that <sBaseRef>.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020703.ShortMessage: The 'comp:unitRef' attribute must be the 'id' of a UnitDefinition

1020704.Message:
The value of a 'comp:metaIdRef' attribute on an <sBaseRef> object must be the value of a 'comp:metaid' attribute on an element contained in the <model> referenced by that <sBaseRef>.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020704.ShortMessage: The 'comp:metaIdRef' attribute must be the 'metaid' of an object

1020705.Message:
If an <sBaseRef> object contains an <sBaseRef> child, the parent <sBaseRef> must point to a <submodel> object, or a <port> that itself points to a <submodel> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.2
1020705.ShortMessage: If <sBaseRef> has a child <sBaseRef> its parent must be a <submodel>

1020706.Message:
The value of a 'comp:portRef' attribute on an SBaseRef object must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020706.ShortMessage: The 'comp:portRef' attribute must have the syntax of an SBML SId

1020707.Message:
The value of a 'comp:idRef' attribute on an SBaseRef object must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020707.ShortMessage: The 'comp:idRef' attribute must have the syntax of an SBML SId

1020708.Message:
The value of a 'comp:unitRef' attribute on an SBaseRef object must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020708.ShortMessage: The 'comp:unitRef' attribute must have the syntax of an SBML SId

1020709.Message:
The value of a 'comp:metaIdRef' attribute on an SBaseRef object must always conform to the syntax of the XML data type ID.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020709.ShortMessage: The 'comp:metaIdRef' attribute must have the syntax of an XML ID

1020710.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, an SBaseRef object may only contain a single <sBaseRef> child.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.2

1020711.Message:
The 'sbaseRef' spelling of an SBaseRef child of an SBaseRef object is considered deprecated, and 'sBaseRef' should be used instead.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.2

1020712.Message:
An <sBaseRef> object must point to another object; that is, a <sBaseRef> object must always have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020712.ShortMessage: An SBaseRef must reference an object.

1020713.Message:
An <sBaseRef> object can only point to one other object; that is, a given <sBaseRef> object can only have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020713.ShortMessage: An SBaseRef must reference only one other object.

1020714.Message:
Any one SBML object may only be referenced in one of the following ways:  referenced by a single <port> object; referenced by a single <deletion> object; referenced by a single <replacedElement>; be the parent of a single <replacedBy> child; be referenced by one or more <replacedBy> objects; or be referenced by one or more <replacedElement> objects all using the 'deletion' attribute.  Essentially, once an object has been referenced in one of these ways it cannot be referenced again.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020714.ShortMessage: Objects may not be referenced by mutiple SBaseRef constructs.

1020801.Message:
A <port> object must point to another object; that is, a <port> object must always have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4.3

1020802.Message:
A <port> object can only point to one other object; that is, a given <port> object can only have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4.3
1020802.ShortMessage: Port must reference only one other object.

1020803.Message:
A <port> object must have a value for the required attribute 'comp:id', and one, and only one, of the attributes 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'.  No other attributes from the Hierarchical Model Composition namespace are permitted on a <port> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4.3

1020804.Message:
Port definitions must be unique; that is, no two <port> objects in a given Model may reference the same object in that Model.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4.3

1020901.Message:
A <deletion> object must point to another object; that is, a <deletion> object must always have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.3

1020902.Message:
A <deletion> object can only point to one other object; that is, a given <deletion> object can only have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.3
1020902.ShortMessage: Deletion must reference only one other object.

1020903.Message:
A <deletion> object must have a value for one, and only one, of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', and 'comp:metaIdRef'.  It may also have the optional attributes 'comp:id' and 'comp:name'.  No other attributes from the Hierarchical Model Composition namespace are permitted on a <deletion> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.3

1021001.Message:
A <replacedElement> object must point to another object; that is, a <replacedElement> object must always have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', 'comp:metaIdRef' or 'comp:deletion'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2

1021002.Message:
A <replacedElement> object can only point to one other object; that is, a given <replacedElement> object can only have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', 'comp:metaIdRef' or 'comp:deletion'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2
1021002.ShortMessage: ReplacedElement must reference only one other object.

1021003.Message:
A <replacedElement> object must have a value for the required attribute 'comp:submodelRef', and a value for one, and only one, of the following attributes: 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', 'comp:metaIdRef', or 'comp:deletion'. It may also have a value for the optional attribute 'comp:conversionFactor'. No other attributes from the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <replacedElement> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2

1021004.Message:
The value of a 'comp:submodelRef' attribute on a <replacedElement> object must be the identifier of a <submodel> present in the <replacedElement> object's parent Model.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2
1021004.ShortMessage: The 'comp:submodelRef' attribute must point to a <submodel>

1021005.Message:
The value of a 'comp:deletion' attribute on a <replacedElement> object must be the identifier of a <deletion> present in the <replacedElement> object's parent Model.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2
1021005.ShortMessage: The 'comp:deletion' attribute must point to a <deletion>

1021006.Message:
The value of a 'comp:conversionFactor' attribute on a <replacedElement> object must be the identifier of a <parameter> present in the <replacedElement> object's parent Model
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2
1021006.ShortMessage: The 'comp:conversionFactor attribute must point to a <parameter>

1021010.Message:
No two <replacedElement> objects in the same Model may reference the same object unless that object is a <deletion>
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2

1021011.Message:
If a <replacedElement> uses the 'comp:deletion' attribute, then it should not also use the 'comp:conversionFactor' attribute.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2

1021101.Message:
A <replacedBy> object must point to another object; that is, a <replacedBy> object must always have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef' or 'comp:metaIdRef'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.4

1021102.Message:
A <replacedBy> object can only point to one other object; that is, a given <replacedBy> object can only have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.4
1021102.ShortMessage: ReplacedBy must reference only one other object.

1021103.Message:
A <replacedBy> object must have a value for the required attribute 'comp:submodelRef', and a value for one, and only one, of the following attributes: 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef' or 'comp:metaIdRef'. No other attributes from the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <replacedBy> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.4

1021104.Message:
The value of a 'comp:submodelRef' attribute on a <replacedBy> object must be the identifier of a <submodel> present in the <replacedBy> object's parent Model.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.4
1021104.ShortMessage: The 'comp:submodelRef' attribute must point to a <submodel>

1021201.Message:
If one element replaces another, whether it is the target of a <replacedBy> element, or whether it has a child <replacedElement>, the SBML class of the replacement element must match the SBML class of the replaced element, with two exceptions: an element of a derived class may replace an object of its base class (for base classes other than SBase), and any SBML class with mathematical meaning may replace a <parameter>. A base class may not replace a derived class, however, nor may a <parameter> replace some other SBML element with mathematical meaning.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.5

1021202.Message:
If one element replaces another, whether it is the target of a <replacedBy> element, or whether it has a child <replacedElement>, if the replaced element has the 'id' attribute set, the replacement !element must also have the 'id' attribute set.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.5
1021202.ShortMessage: Replaced IDs must be replaced with IDs.

1021203.Message:
If one element replaces another, whether it is the target of a <replacedBy> element, or whether it has a child <replacedElement>, if the replaced element has the 'metaid' attribute set, the replacement element must also have the 'metaid' attribute set.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.5
1021203.ShortMessage: Replaced metaids must be replaced with metaids.

1021204.Message:
If one element replaces another, whether it is the target of a <replacedBy> element, or whether it has a child <replacedElement>, if the replaced element has an identifier attribute from some other SBML package set, the replacement element must also have that same identifier attribute set.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.5
1021204.ShortMessage: Replaced package IDs must be replaced with package IDs.

1090101.Message: The external model referenced in this model could not be resolved.

1090102.Message: The external document referenced in this model did not contain any models.

1090103.Message: An external model definition referenced by an external model definition in this model was itself unresolvable.

1090104.Message: Errors arose during the attempt to flatten the model.

1090105.Message:
The interpretation the Hierarchical Model Composition constructs to produce a kind of 'flattened' version of the model devoid of the comp package constructs must produce a valid SBML Level 3 model.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Appendix A1

1090106.Message: Due to the need to instantiate models, modelDefinitions, submodels etc. for the purposes of validation it is problematic to reliably report line numbers when performing validation on models using the Hierarchical Model Composition package.

1090107.ShortMessage: Flattening not implemented for required package.

1090108.Message: The CompFlatteningConverter has encountered an unrequired package for which libSBML does not recognize the information.
1090108.ShortMessage: Flattening not implemented for unrequired package.

1090109.Message: The CompFlatteningConverter has encountered an unrequired package for which the necessary routines to allow flattening have not yet been implemented.
1090109.ShortMessage: Flattening not implemented for unrequired package.

1090110.Message: The CompFlatteningConverter has encountered a required package for which the necessary routines to allow flattening have not yet been implemented.
1090110.ShortMessage: Flattening not implemented for required package.

1090111.Message: The CompFlatteningConverter has encountered an unknown reference which may be due to the presence of an unknown package.
1090111.ShortMessage: Flattening reference may come from package.

1090112.Message: The software used to process this hierarchical model used the deprecated function performDeletions to do so.  Unfortunately, it is impossible to properly use this function as it was originally designed, without some models either causing the program to crash, or causing them to be interpreted incorrectly.  Instead, the software should use collectDeletionsAndDeleteCompConstructs, in conjunction with collectRenameAndConvertReplacements and removeCollectedElements to properly process hierarchical models.

1090113.Message: The software used to process this hierarchical model used the deprecated function performReplacementsAndConversions to do so.  Unfortunately, it is impossible to properly use this function as it was originally designed, without some models either causing the program to crash, or causing them to be interpreted incorrectly.  Instead, the software should use collectDeletionsAndDeleteCompConstructs, in conjunction with collectRenameAndConvertReplacements and removeCollectedElements to properly process hierarchical models.

1090114.Message: The model contained a deletion whose subelement was replaced.  This is perfectly legal, but unfortunately, the subroutine used to implement this actually removed the deleted element and all of its children before replacing the child, making it impossible to discover any IDs that need to be replaced.
1090114.ShortMessage: Element deleted before a subelement could be replaced.

1090115.Message: The value of a 'comp:idRef' attribute on an <sBaseRef> object must be the identifier of an object contained in (that is, within the SId namespace of) the <model> referenced by that <sBaseRef>. This includes objects with 'id' attributes defined in packages other than SBML Level 3 Core or the Hierarchical Model Composition package.
1090115.ShortMessage: The 'comp:idRef' attribute must be the 'id' of a model element

1090116.Message: The value of a 'comp:metaIdRef' attribute on an <sBaseRef> object must be the value of a 'comp:metaid' attribute on an element contained in the <model> referenced by that <sBaseRef>.
1090116.ShortMessage: The 'comp:metaIdRef' attribute must be the 'metaid' of a model element

1210101.Message:
To conform to the Spatial Processes Package specification for SBML Level 3 Version 1, an SBML document must declare 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/spatial/version1' as the XMLNamespace to use for elements of this package.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section 3.1
1210101.ShortMessage: The Spatial namespace is not correctly declared.

1210102.Message:
Wherever they appear in an SBML document, elements and attributes from the Spatial Processes Package must use the 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/spatial/version1' namespace, declaring so either explicitly or implicitly.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section 3.1

1210301.Message:
(Extends validation rule #10301 in the SBML Level 3 Core specification. TO DO list scope of ids)
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1210302.Message:
The value of a 'spatial:id' must conform to the syntax of the <sbml> data type 'SId'
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220101.Message:
In all SBML documents using the Spatial Processes Package, the <sbml> object must have the 'spatial:required' attribute.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220102.Message:
The value of attribute 'spatial:required' on the <sbml> object must be of data type 'boolean'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section
1220102.ShortMessage: The spatial:required attribute must be Boolean

1220103.Message:
The value of attribute 'spatial:required' on the <sbml> object must be set to 'true'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220201.Message:
A <model> object may contain one and only one instance of the <geometry> element. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Spatial Processes namespaces are permitted on a <model> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220301.Message:
A <compartment> object may contain one and only one instance of the <compartmentMapping> element. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Spatial Processes namespaces are permitted on a <compartment> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220401.Message:
A <species> object may have the optional attribute 'spatial:isSpatial'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Spatial Processes namespaces are permitted on a <species> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220402.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:isSpatial' on a <species> must have a value of data type 'boolean'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220501.Message:
A <parameter> object may contain one and only one instance of each of the <spatialSymbolReference,> <advectionCoefficient,> <boundaryCondition> and <diffusionCoefficient> elements. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Spatial Processes namespaces are permitted on a <parameter> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220601.Message:
A <reaction> object must have the required attribute 'spatial:isLocal'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Spatial Processes namespaces are permitted on a <reaction> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220602.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:isLocal' on a <reaction> must have a value of data type 'boolean'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220701.Message:
A <domainType> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <domainType>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220702.Message:
A <domainType> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <domainType>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220703.Message:
A <domainType> object must have the required attributes 'spatial:id' and 'spatial:spatialDimensions', and may have the optional attribute 'spatial:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Spatial Processes namespaces are permitted on a <domainType> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220704.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:spatialDimensions' on a <domainType> must have a value of data type 'integer'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220705.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:name' on a <domainType> must have a value of data type 'string'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220801.Message:
A <domain> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <domain>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220802.Message:
A <domain> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <domain>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220803.Message:
A <domain> object must have the required attributes 'spatial:id' and 'spatial:domainType', and may have the optional attribute 'spatial:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Spatial Processes namespaces are permitted on a <domain> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220804.Message:
A <domain> object may contain one and only one instance of the <listOfInteriorPoints> element. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Spatial Processes namespaces are permitted on a <domain> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220805.Message:
The value of the attribute 'spatial:domainType' of a <domain> object must be the identifier of an existing <domainType> object defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section
1220805.ShortMessage: The attribute 'domainType' must point to DomainType object.

1220806.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:name' on a <domain> must have a value of data type 'string'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220807.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotations subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfInteriorPoints> container object may only contain <interiorPoint> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220808.Message:
A <listOfInteriorPoints> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <listOfInteriorPoints> object.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220901.Message:
An <interiorPoint> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on an <interiorPoint>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220902.Message:
An <interiorPoint> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on an <interiorPoint>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220903.Message:
An <interiorPoint> object must have the required attribute 'spatial:coordOne', and may have the optional attributes 'spatial:coordTwo' and 'spatial:coordThree'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Spatial Processes namespaces are permitted on an <interiorPoint> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220904.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:coordOne' on an <interiorPoint> must have a value of data type 'double'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220905.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:coordTwo' on an <interiorPoint> must have a value of data type 'double'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1220906.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:coordThree' on an <interiorPoint> must have a value of data type 'double'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221001.Message:
A <boundary> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <boundary>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221002.Message:
A <boundary> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <boundary>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221003.Message:
A <boundary> object must have the required attributes 'spatial:id' and 'spatial:value', and may have the optional attribute 'spatial:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Spatial Processes namespaces are permitted on a <boundary> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221004.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:value' on a <boundary> must have a value of data type 'double'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221005.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:name' on a <boundary> must have a value of data type 'string'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221101.Message:
An <adjacentDomains> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on an <adjacentDomains>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221102.Message:
An <adjacentDomains> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on an <adjacentDomains>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221103.Message:
An <adjacentDomains> object must have the required attributes 'spatial:id', 'spatial:domainOne' and 'spatial:domainTwo', and may have the optional attribute 'spatial:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Spatial Processes namespaces are permitted on an <adjacentDomains> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221104.Message:
The value of the attribute 'spatial:domainOne' of an <adjacentDomains> object must be the identifier of an existing <domain> object defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section
1221104.ShortMessage: The attribute 'domain1' must point to Domain object.

1221105.Message:
The value of the attribute 'spatial:domainTwo' of an <adjacentDomains> object must be the identifier of an existing <domain> object defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section
1221105.ShortMessage: The attribute 'domain2' must point to Domain object.

1221106.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:name' on an <adjacentDomains> must have a value of data type 'string'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221201.Message:
A <geometryDefinition> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <geometryDefinition>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221202.Message:
A <geometryDefinition> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <geometryDefinition>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221203.Message:
A <geometryDefinition> object must have the required attributes 'spatial:id' and 'spatial:isActive', and may have the optional attribute 'spatial:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Spatial Processes namespaces are permitted on a <geometryDefinition> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221204.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:isActive' on a <geometryDefinition> must have a value of data type 'boolean'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221205.Message:
The attribute 'spatial:name' on a <geometryDefinition> must have a value of data type 'string'.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221301.Message:
A <compartmentMapping> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <compartmentMapping>.
Reference: L3V1 Spatial V1 Section

1221302.Message:
