Wherever they appear in an SBML document, elements and attributes from the Distributions Package must use the 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/distrib/version1' namespace, declaring so either explicitly or implicitly.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section 3.1

1510301.Message:
(Extends validation rule #10301 in the SBML Level 3 Core specification. TO DO list scope of ids)
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1510302.Message:
The value of a 'distrib:id' must conform to the syntax of the <sbml> data type 'SId'
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520101.Message:
In all SBML documents using the Distributions Package, the <sbml> object must have the 'distrib:required' attribute.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520102.Message:
The value of attribute 'distrib:required' on the <sbml> object must be of data type 'boolean'.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section
1520102.ShortMessage: The distrib:required attribute must be Boolean

1520103.Message:
The value of attribute 'distrib:required' on the <sbml> object must be set to 'true'.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520201.Message:
A 'SBase' object may contain one and only one instance of the <listOfUncertainties> element. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Distributions namespaces are permitted on a 'SBase' object. 
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520202.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotations subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfUncertainties> container object may only contain <uncertainty> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520203.Message:
A <listOfUncertainties> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <listOfUncertainties> object.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520301.Message:
An <uncertParameter> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on an <uncertParameter>.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520302.Message:
An <uncertParameter> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on an <uncertParameter>.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520303.Message:
An <uncertParameter> object may have the optional attributes 'distrib:value', 'distrib:var', 'distrib:units', 'distrib:type' and 'distrib:definitionURL'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Distributions namespaces are permitted on an <uncertParameter> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520304.Message:
An <uncertParameter> object may contain one and only one instance of the <listOfUncertParameters> element. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Distributions namespaces are permitted on an <uncertParameter> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520305.Message:
The attribute 'distrib:value' on an <uncertParameter> must have a value of data type 'double'.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520306.Message:
The value of the attribute 'distrib:var' of an <uncertParameter> object must be the identifier of an existing object derived from the 'SBase' class and defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section
1520306.ShortMessage: The attribute 'var' must point to SBase object.

1520307.Message:
The value of the attribute 'distrib:units' on an <uncertParameter> must have a taken from the following: the identifier of a <unitDefinition> object in the enclosing <model,> or one of the base units in SBML.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520308.Message:
The value of the attribute 'distrib:type' of an <uncertParameter> object must conform to the syntax of SBML data type 'UncertType' and may only take on the allowed values of 'UncertType' defined in SBML; that is, the value must be one of the following: 'distribution', 'externalParameter', 'coeffientOfVariation', 'kurtosis', 'mean', 'median', 'mode', 'sampleSize', 'skewness', 'standardDeviation', 'standardError', 'variance', 'confidenceInterval', 'credibleInterval', 'interquartileRange' or 'range'.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520309.Message:
The attribute 'distrib:definitionURL' on an <uncertParameter> must have a value of data type 'string'.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520310.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotations subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfUncertParameters> container object may only contain <uncertParameter> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520311.Message:
A <listOfUncertParameters> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <listOfUncertParameters> object.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520401.Message:
An <uncertainty> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on an <uncertainty>.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520402.Message:
An <uncertainty> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on an <uncertainty>.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520403.Message:
An <uncertainty> object may contain one and only one instance of the <listOfUncertParameters> element. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Distributions namespaces are permitted on an <uncertainty> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520501.Message:
An <uncertSpan> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on an <uncertSpan>.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520502.Message:
An <uncertSpan> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on an <uncertSpan>.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520503.Message:
An <uncertSpan> object may have the optional attributes 'distrib:varLower', 'distrib:valueLower', 'distrib:varUpper' and 'distrib:valueUpper'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Distributions namespaces are permitted on an <uncertSpan> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520504.Message:
The value of the attribute 'distrib:varLower' of an <uncertSpan> object must be the identifier of an existing object derived from the 'SBase' class and defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section
1520504.ShortMessage: The attribute 'varLower' must point to SBase object.

1520505.Message:
The attribute 'distrib:valueLower' on an <uncertSpan> must have a value of data type 'double'.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520506.Message:
The value of the attribute 'distrib:varUpper' of an <uncertSpan> object must be the identifier of an existing object derived from the 'SBase' class and defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section
1520506.ShortMessage: The attribute 'varUpper' must point to SBase object.

1520507.Message:
The attribute 'distrib:valueUpper' on an <uncertSpan> must have a value of data type 'double'.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520601.Message:
A <distribBase> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <distribBase>.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520602.Message:
A <distribBase> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <distribBase>.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520603.Message:
A <distribBase> object may have the optional attributes 'distrib:id' and 'distrib:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Distributions namespaces are permitted on a <distribBase> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

1520604.Message:
The attribute 'distrib:name' on a <distribBase> must have a value of data type 'string'.
Reference: L3V1 Distrib V1 Section

2010101.Message:
To conform to Version 1 of the Flux Balance Constraints package specification for SBML Level 3, an SBML document must declare the use of the following XML Namespace: 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/fbc/version1'
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.1
2010101.ShortMessage: The fbc ns is not correctly declared

2010102.Message:
Wherever they appear in an SBML document, elements and attributes from the Flux Balance Constraints package must be declared either implicitly or explicitly to be in the XML namespace 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/fbc/version1'
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.1

2010301.Message:
(Extends validation rule #10301 in the SBML Level 3 Version 1 Core specification.) Within a <model> object the values of the attributes id and fbc:id on every instance of the following classes of objects must be unique across the set of all id and fbc:id attribute values of all such objects in a model: the model itself, plus all contained <functionDefinition>, <compartment>, <species>, <reaction>, <speciesReference>, <modifierSpeciesReference>, <event>, and <parameter> objects, plus the <fluxBound>, <objective>, <fluxObjective>, <geneProduct> and <geneProductAssociation> objects defined by the Flux Balance Constraints package.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.2

2010302.Message:
The value of a fbc:id attribute must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.2

2020101.Message:
In all SBML documents using the Flux Balance Constraints package, the SBML object must include a value for the attribute 'fbc:required'.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 4.1.2

2020102.Message:
The value of attribute 'fbc:required' on the SBML object must be of the data type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 4.1.2
2020102.ShortMessage: The fbc:required attribute must be Boolean

2020103.Message:
The value of attribute 'fbc:required' on the SBML object must be set to 'false'.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.1

2020201.Message:
There may be at most one instance of each of the following kinds of objects within a <model> object using Flux Balance Constraints: <listOfFluxBounds> (V1 only), <listOfObjectives> and <listOfGeneProducts> (V2).
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.3
2020201.ShortMessage: One of each list of allowed

2020202.Message:
The various ListOf subobjects with a <model> object are optional, but if present, these container object must not be empty. Specifically, if any of the following classes of objects are present on the <model>, it must not be empty: <listOfFluxBounds> (V1 only), <listOfObjectives> and <listOfGeneProducts> (V2).
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.3

2020203.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfFluxBounds> container object may only contain <fluxBound> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.3

2020204.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfObjectives> container object may only contain <objective> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.3

2020205.Message:
A <listOfFluxBounds> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <listOfFluxBounds> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.3

2020206.Message:
A <listOfFluxBounds> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core. Additionally the <listOfObjectives> must contain the attribute 'activeObjective'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <listOfFluxBounds> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.3

2020207.Message:
The value of attribute 'fbc:activeObjective' on the <listOfObjectives> object must be of the data type SIdRef.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.2.2

2020208.Message:
The value of attribute 'fbc:activeObjective' on the <listOfObjectives> object must be the identifier of an existing <objective>.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.2.2

2020209.Message: A <model> object must have the required attributes 'strict'. No other attributes from the Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <model> object.

2020210.Message: The attribute 'fbc:strict' on the <model> object must have a value of datatype Boolean.

2020211.Message: Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfGeneProducts> container object may only contain <geneProduct> objects.

2020212.Message: A <listOfGeneProducts> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <listOfGeneProducts> object.

2020301.Message:
A SBML <species> object may have the optional attributes 'fbc:charge' and 'fbc:chemicalFormula'. No other attributes from the Flux Balance Constraints namespaces are permitted on a <species>. 
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.4

2020302.Message:
The value of attribute 'fbc:charge' on SBML <species> object must be of the data type integer.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.4

2020303.Message:
The value of attribute 'fbc:chemicalFormula' on the SBML <species> object must be set to a string consisting only of atomic names or user defined compounds and their occurrence.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.4

2020401.Message:
A <fluxBound> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <fluxBound>.
Reference: L3V1 Core, Section 3.2
2020401.ShortMessage: <fluxBound> may only have 'metaId' and 'sboTerm' from L3 namespace

2020402.Message:
A <fluxBound> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <fluxBound>.
Reference: L3V1 Core, Section 3.2
2020402.ShortMessage: <fluxBound> may only have <notes> and <annotations> from L3 Core

2020403.Message:
A <fluxBound> object must have the required attributes 'fbc:reaction', 'fbc:operation' and 'fbc:value', and may have the optional attributes 'fbc:id' and 'fbc:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <fluxBound> object.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5

2020404.Message:
The attribute 'fbc:reaction' of a <fluxBound> must be of the data type SIdRef.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5

2020405.Message:
The attribute 'fbc:name' of a <fluxBound> must be of the data type string.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5
2020405.ShortMessage: The attribute 'fbc:name' must be of the data type string

2020406.Message:
The attribute 'fbc:operation' of a <fluxBound> must be of the data type FbcOperation and thus it's value must be one of 'lessEqual', 'greaterEqual' or 'equal'.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5
2020406.ShortMessage: The attribute 'fbc:operation' must be of data type FbcOperation

2020407.Message:
The attribute 'fbc:value' of a <fluxBound> must be of the data type double.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5
2020407.ShortMessage: The attribute 'fbc:value' must be of the data type double

2020408.Message:
The value of the attribute 'fbc:reaction' of a <fluxBound> object must be the identifier of an existing <reaction> object defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5

2020409.Message:
The combined set of all <fluxBound>'s with identical values for 'fbc:reaction' must be consistent. That is while it is possible to define a lower and an upper bound for a reaction, it is not possible to define multiple lower or upper bounds.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5
2020409.ShortMessage: Conflicting set of FluxBounds for a reaction

2020501.Message:
An <objective> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an <objective>. 
Reference: L3V1 Core, Section 3.2
2020501.ShortMessage: <objective> may only have 'metaId' and 'sboTerm' from L3 namespace

2020502.Message:
An <objective> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an <objective>.
Reference: L3V1 Core, Section 3.2
2020502.ShortMessage: <objective> may only have <notes> and <annotations> from L3 Core

2020503.Message:
An <objective> object must have the required attributes 'fbc:id' and 'fbc:type' and may have the optional attribute 'fbc:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on an <objective> object.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.6

2020504.Message:
The attribute 'fbc:name' on an <objective> must be of the data type 'string'. 
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.6
2020504.ShortMessage: The attribute 'fbc:name' must be of the data type string

2020505.Message:
The attribute 'fbc:type' on an <objective> must be of the data type FbcType and thus its value must be one of 'minimize' or 'maximize.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.6
2020505.ShortMessage: The attribute 'fbc:type' must be of data type FbcType.

2020506.Message:
An <objective> object must have one and only one instance of the <listOfFluxObjectives> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.6

2020507.Message:
The <listOfFluxObjectives> subobject within an <objective> object must not be empty.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.6

2020508.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfFluxObjectives> container object may only contain <fluxObjective> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.6

2020509.Message:
A <listOfFluxObjectives> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <listOfFluxObjectives> object
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.6
2020509.ShortMessage: <listOfFluxObjectives> may only have 'metaId' and 'sboTerm' from L3 core

2020601.Message:
A <fluxObjective> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <fluxObjective>. 
Reference: L3V1 Core, Section 3.2
2020601.ShortMessage: <fluxObjective> may only have 'metaId' and 'sboTerm' from L3 namespace

2020602.Message:
A <fluxObjective> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <fluxObjective>.
Reference: L3V1 Core, Section 3.2
2020602.ShortMessage: <fluxObjective> may only have <notes> and <annotations> from L3 Core

2020603.Message:
A <fluxObjective> object must have the required attributes 'fbc:reaction' and 'fbc:coefficient', and may have the optional attributes 'fbc:id' and 'fbc:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <fluxObjective> object.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.7

2020604.Message:
The attribute 'fbc:name' on a <fluxObjective> must be of the data type 'string'.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.7
2020604.ShortMessage: The attribute 'fbc:name' must be of the data type string

2020605.Message:
The value of the attribute 'fbc:reaction' of a <fluxObjective> object must conform to the syntax of the SBML data type 'SIdRef'.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.7

2020606.Message:
The value of the attribute 'fbc:reaction' of a <fluxObjective> object must be the identifier of an existing <reaction> object defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.7

2020607.Message:
The value of the attribute 'fbc:coefficient' of a <fluxObjective> object must conform to the syntax of the SBML data type 'double'.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.7
2020607.ShortMessage: The attribute 'fbc:coefficient' must be of the data type double

2020608.Message: When the value of the <model> 'fbc:strict' attribute is true, the value of the attribute 'fbc:coefficient' of a <fluxObjective> object must not be set to 'NaN', 'INF' or '-INF'.
2020608.ShortMessage: The 'fbc:coefficient' must be declared when strict

2020701.Message: There may be at most one instance of a <GeneProductAssociation> within a <Reaction> object using Flux BalanceConstraints.

2020702.Message: An SBML <Reaction> object may have the optional attributes 'fbc:lowerFluxBound' and 'fbc:upperFluxBound'. No other attributes from the Flux Balance Constraints namespaces are permitted on a <Reaction>.

2020703.Message: The attribute 'fbc:lowerFluxBound' of a <Reaction> must be of the data type 'SIdRef'.

2020704.Message: The attribute 'fbc:upperFluxBound' of a <Reaction> must be of the data type 'SIdRef'.

2020705.Message: The attribute 'fbc:lowerFluxBound' of a <Reaction> must point to an existing <Parameter> in the model.

2020706.Message: The attribute 'fbc:upperFluxBound' of a <Reaction> must point to an existing <Parameter> in the model.

2020707.Message: When the value of the <Model>s 'fbc:strict' attribute is 'true', a <Reaction> must define the attributes 'fbc:lowerFluxBound' and 'fbc:upperFluxBound'.
2020707.ShortMessage: Reaction must have bounds when strict

2020708.Message: When the value of the <Model>s 'fbc:strict' attribute is 'true', the <Parameter> objects referred to by the attributes 'fbc:lowerFluxBound' and 'fbc:upperFluxBound' must have their 'constant' attribute set to 'true'.

2020709.Message: When the value of the <Model>s 'fbc:strict' attribute is 'true', the <Parameter> objects referred to by the attributes 'fbc:lowerFluxBound' and 'fbc:upperFluxBound' must have a defined value for their 'value' attribute, which may not be 'NaN'.
2020709.ShortMessage: Reaction bounds must have values when strict

2020710.Message: When the value of the <Model>s 'fbc:strict' attribute is 'true', the <Parameter> objects referred to by the attributes 'fbc:lowerFluxBound' and 'fbc:upperFluxBound' may not be targeted by an <InitialAssignment>.
2020710.ShortMessage: Reaction bounds not assigned when strict

2020711.Message: When the value of the <Model>s 'fbc:strict' attribute is 'true', the <Parameter> objects referred to by the attribute 'fbc:lowerFluxBound' may not have the value 'INF'.
2020711.ShortMessage: LowerBound cannot be INF when strict

2020712.Message: When the value of the <Model>s 'fbc:strict' attribute is 'true', the <Parameter> object referred to by the attribute 'fbc:upperFluxBound' may not have the value '-INF'.

2020713.Message: When the value of the <Model>s 'fbc:strict' attribute is 'true', the <Parameter> object referred to by the attribute 'fbc:lowerFluxBound' must be less than or equal to the value of the <Parameter> object referred to by the attribute 'fbc:upperFluxBound' .
2020713.ShortMessage: LowerBound less than upperBound when strict

2020714.Message: When the value of the <Model>s 'fbc:strict' attribute is 'true', the 'constant' attribute of <SpeciesReference> elements of a <Reaction> must be set to 'true'.
2020714.ShortMessage: SpeciesReferences must be constant when strict

2020715.Message: When the value of the <Model>s 'fbc:strict' attribute is 'true', the value of a <SpeciesReference>'s 'stoichiometry> attribute must not be set to 'NaN',  '-INF' or  'INF'.
2020715.ShortMessage: Stoichiometry of SpeciesReferences must be real valued when strict

2020716.Message: When the value of the <Model>s 'fbc:strict' attribute is 'true', the <SpeciesReference> elements of a <Reaction> may not be targeted by an <InitialAssignment>.
2020716.ShortMessage: SpeciesReference not target of InitialAssignment when strict

2020801.Message: A <GeneProductAssociation> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <GeneProductAssociation.

2020802.Message: A <GeneProductAssociation> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <GeneProductAssociation.

2020803.Message: A <GeneProductAssociation> object may have the optional attributes 'fbc:id' and 'fbc:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <GeneProductAssociation> object.

2020804.Message: The attribute 'fbc:id' on a <GeneProductAssociation> must be of the data type 'SId'.

2020805.Message: A <GeneProductAssociation> object must have one and only one of the concrete <Association> objects:  <GeneProductRef>, <And> or <Or>.

2020806.Message: The attribute 'fbc:name' on a <GeneProductAssociation> must be of the data type 'string'.

2020901.Message: A <GeneProductRef> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <GeneProductRef>.

2020902.Message: A <GeneProductRef> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <GeneProductRef>.

2020903.Message: A <GeneProductRef> object must have the required attribute 'fbc:geneProduct' and may have the optional attribute 'fbc:id'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <> object.

2020904.Message: The attribute 'fbc:geneProduct' on a <GeneProductRef> must be of the data type 'SIdRef'.

2020908.Message: The attribute 'fbc:geneProduct' on a <GeneProductRef>  if set, must refer to 'id' of a <GeneProduct> in the <Model>.

2021001.Message: An <And> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an <GeneAnd.

2021002.Message: An <And> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an <And>.

2021003.Message: An <And> object must have two or more concrete <Association> objects: <GeneProductRef>, <And>, or <Or>. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on an <And> object.
2021003.ShortMessage: <And> must have at least two child elements

2021101.Message: An <Or> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an <Or>.

2021102.Message: An <Or> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an <Or>.

2021103.Message: An <Or> object must have two or more concrete <Association> objects: <GeneProductRef>, <And>, or <Or>. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on an <Or> object.
2021103.ShortMessage: <Or> must have at least two child elements

2021201.Message: A <GeneProduct> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <GeneProduct>.

2021202.Message: A <GeneProduct> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <GeneProduct>.

2021203.Message: A <GeneProduct> object must have the required attributes 'fbc:id' and 'fbc:label' may have the optional attributes 'fbc:name' and 'fbc:associatedSpecies'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <GeneProduct> object.

2021204.Message: The attribute 'fbc:label' on a <GeneProduct> must be of the data type 'string'.

2021205.Message: The attribute 'fbc:label' on a <GeneProduct> must be unique among the set of all <GeneProduct> elements defined in the <Model>.

2021206.Message: The attribute 'fbc:name' on a <GeneProduct> must be of the data type 'string'.

2021207.Message: The attribute 'fbc:associatedSpecies' on a <GeneProduct> must be the identifier of an existing <Species> defined in the enclosing <Model>.

3010101.Message:
To conform to Version 1 of the Qualitative Models package specification for SBML Level 3, an SBML document must declare the use of the following XML Namespace: 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/qual/version1'
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.1
3010101.ShortMessage: The qual ns is not correctly declared

3010102.Message:
Wherever they appear in an SBML document, elements and attributes from the Qualitative Models package must be declared either implicitly or explicitly to be in the XML namespace 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/qual/version1'
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.1

3010201.Message:
The MathML <math> element in a <functionTerm> object should evaluate to a value of type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.5

3010202.Message:
The MathML <math> element in a <functionTerm> object should not use the <csymbol> elements 'time' and 'delay' as these explicitly introduce time into the model. As yet time is not considered within the Qualitative Models package specification.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.5
3010202.ShortMessage: CSymbol time or delay not allowed

3010301.Message:
(Extends validation rule #10301 in the SBML Level 3 Version 1 Core specification.) Within a <model> the values of the attributes 'id' and 'qual:id' on every instance of the following classes of objects must be unique across the set of all 'id' and 'qual:id' attribute values of all such objects in a model: the <model> itself, plus all contained <functionDefinition>, <compartment>, <species>, <reaction>, <speciesReference>, <modifierSpeciesReference>, <event>, and <parameter> objects, plus the <qualitativeSpecies>, <transition>, <input> and <output> objects defined by the Qualitative Models package.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.7

3020101.Message:
In all SBML documents using the Qualitative Models package, the SBML object must include a value for the attribute 'qual:required' attribute.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 4.1.2

3020102.Message:
The value of attribute 'qual:required' on the SBML object must be of the data type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 4.1.2
3020102.ShortMessage: The qual:required attribute must be Boolean

3020103.Message:
The value of attribute 'qual:required' on the SBML object must be set to 'true' if if the model contains any <transition> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.1
3020103.ShortMessage: The qual:required attribute must be 'true' if math changes

3020201.Message:
There may be at most one instance of each of the following kinds of objects within a <model> object using Qualitative Models: <listOfTransitions> and <listOfQualitativeSpecies>.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.4

3020202.Message:
The various ListOf subobjects with a <model> object are optional, but if present, these container object must not be empty.  Specifically, if any of the following classes of objects are present on the <model>, it must not be empty: <listOfQualitativeSpecies> and <listOfTransitions>.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.4

3020203.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfTransitions> container object may only contain <transition> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.4

3020204.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfQualitativeSpecies> container object may only contain <qualitativeSpecies> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.4

3020205.Message:
A <listOfQualitativeSpecies> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <listOfQualitativeSpecies> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.4

3020206.Message:
A <listOfTransitions> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <listOfTransitions> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.4

3020301.Message:
A <qualitativeSpecies> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <qualitativeSpecies> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.5

3020302.Message:
A <qualitativeSpecies> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <qualitativeSpecies>.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.5

3020303.Message:
A <qualitativeSpecies> object must have the required attributes 'qual:id', 'qual:compartment' and 'qual:constant', and may have the optional attributes 'qual:name', 'qual:initialLevel' and 'qual:maxLevel'.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <qualitativeSpecies> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.5

3020304.Message:
The attribute 'qual:constant' in <qualitativeSpecies> must be of the data type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.5

3020305.Message:
The attribute 'qual:name' in <qualitativeSpecies> must be of the data type string.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.5

3020306.Message:
The attribute 'qual:initialLevel' in <qualitativeSpecies> must be of the data type integer.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.5

3020307.Message:
The attribute 'qual:maxLevel' in <qualitativeSpecies> must be of the data type integer.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.5

3020308.Message:
The value of the attribute 'qual:compartment' in a <qualitativeSpecies> object must be the identifier of an existing <compartment> object defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.5

3020309.Message:
The value of the attribute 'qual:initialLevel' in a <qualitativeSpecies> object cannot be greater than the value of the 'qual:maxLevel' attribute for the given <qualitativeSpecies> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.5

3020310.Message:
A <qualitativeSpecies> with attribute 'qual:constant' set to 'true' can only be referred to by an <input>. It cannot be the subject of an <output> in a <transition>. 
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.5

3020311.Message:
A <qualitativeSpecies> that is referenced by an <output> with the 'qual:transitionEffect' attribute set to 'assignmentLevel' should not be referenced by any other <output> with the same 'transitionEffect' throughout the set of transitions for the containing model. 
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.2
3020311.ShortMessage: A <qualitativeSpecies> can only be assigned once.

3020312.Message:
The attribute 'qual:initialLevel' in <qualitativeSpecies> must not be negative. 
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.5

3020313.Message:
The attribute 'qual:maxLevel' in <qualitativeSpecies> must not be negative. 
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.5

3020401.Message:
A <transition> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <transition> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020402.Message:
A <transition> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <transition>.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020403.Message:
A <transition> object may have the optional attributes 'qual:name' and 'qual:id'.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <transition> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020404.Message:
The attribute 'qual:name' in <transition> must be of the data type string.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020405.Message:
A <transition> must have one and only one instance of the <listOfFunctionTerms> objects and may have at most one instance of the <listOfInputs> and <listOfOutputs> objects from the Qualitative Models namespace.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020406.Message:
The <listOfInputs> and <listOfOutputs> subobjects on a <transition> object are optional, but if present, these container object must not be empty.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020407.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfInputs> container object may only contain <input> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020408.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfOutputs> container object may only contain <output> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020409.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfFunctionTerms> container object must contain one and only one <defaultTerm> object and then may only contain <functionTerm> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020410.Message:
A <listOfInputs> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <listOfInputs> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020411.Message:
A <listOfOutputs> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <listOfOutputs> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020412.Message:
A <listOfFunctionTerms> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <listOfFunctionTerms> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020413.Message:
No element of the <listOfFunctionTerms> object may cause the level of a <qualitativeSpecies> to exceed the value 'qual:maxLevel' attribute.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020414.Message:
No element of the <listOfFunctionTerms> object may cause the level of a <qualitativeSpecies> to become negative.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6

3020501.Message:
An <input> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on an <input> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.1

3020502.Message:
An <input> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on an <input>.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.1

3020503.Message:
An <input> object must have the required attributes 'qual:qualitativeSpecies' as well as 'qual:transitionEffect' and may have the optional attributes 'qual:id', 'qual:name', 'qual:sign' and 'qual:thresholdLevel'.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on an <input> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.1

3020504.Message:
The attribute 'qual:name' in <input> must be of the data type string.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.1

3020505.Message:
The value of the attribute 'qual:sign' of an <input> object must conform to the syntax of the SBML data type 'sign' and may only take on the allowed values of 'sign' defined in SBML; that is, the value must be one of the following: 'positive', 'negative', 'dual' or 'unknown'.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.1

3020506.Message:
The value of the attribute 'qual:transitionEffect' of an <input> object must conform to the syntax of the SBML data type 'transitionInputEffect' and may only take on the allowed values of 'transitionInputEffect' defined in SBML; that is, the value must be one of the following: 'none' or 'consumption'.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.1

3020507.Message:
The attribute 'qual:thresholdLevel' in <input> must be of the data type 'integer'.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.1
3020507.ShortMessage: Attribute 'thresholdLevel' on <input> must be non negative integer.

3020508.Message:
The value of the attribute 'qual:qualitativeSpecies' in an <input> object must be the identifier of an existing <qualitativeSpecies> object defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.1
3020508.ShortMessage: Attribute 'qualitativeSpecies' on <input> must refer to existing

3020509.Message:
An <input> that refers to a <qualitativeSpecies> that has a 'qual:constant' attribute set to 'true' cannot have the attribute 'qual:transitionEffect' set to 'consumption'.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.1

3020510.Message:
The attribute 'qual:thresholdLevel' in <input> must not be negative.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.1
3020510.ShortMessage: Attribute 'thresholdLevel' on <input> must be non negative integer.

3020601.Message:
An <output> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on an <output> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.2

3020602.Message:
An <output> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on an <output>.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.1

3020603.Message:
An <output> object must have the required attributes 'qual:qualitativeSpecies' as well as 'qual:transitionEffect' and may have the optional attributes 'qual:id', 'qual:name' and 'qual:outputLevel'.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on an <output> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.2

3020604.Message:
The attribute 'qual:name' in <output> must be of the data type string.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.2

3020605.Message:
The value of the attribute 'qual:transitionEffect' of an <output> object must conform to the syntax of the SBML data type 'transitionOutputEffect' and may only take on the allowed values of 'transitionOutputEffect' defined in SBML; that is, the value must be one of the following: 'production' or 'assignmentLevel'.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.2

3020606.Message:
The attribute 'qual:outputLevel' in <output> must be of the data type 'integer'.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.2
3020606.ShortMessage: Attribute 'outputLevel' on <output> must be non negative integer.

3020607.Message:
The value of the attribute 'qual:qualitativeSpecies' in an <output> object must be the identifier of an existing <qualitativeSpecies> object defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.2
3020607.ShortMessage: Attribute 'qualitativeSpecies' on <output> must refer to existing

3020608.Message:
The <qualitativeSpecies> referred to by the attribute 'qual:qualitativeSpecies' in an <output> object must have the value of its 'qual:constant' attribute set to 'false'.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.2

3020609.Message:
When the value of the attribute 'qual:transitionEffect' of an <output> object is set to the value 'production' the attribute 'qual:outputLevel' for that particular <output> object must have a value set.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.2

3020610.Message:
The attribute 'qual:outputLevel' in <output> must not be negative.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.2
3020610.ShortMessage: Attribute 'outputLevel' on <output> must be non negative integer.

3020701.Message:
A <defaultTerm> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <defaultTerm> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.4

3020702.Message:
A <defaultTerm> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <defaultTerm>.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.4

3020703.Message:
A <defaultTerm> object must have the required attributes 'qual:resultLevel'.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <defaultTerm> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.4

3020704.Message:
The attribute 'qual:resultLevel' in <defaultTerm> must be of the data type 'integer'.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.4
3020704.ShortMessage: Attribute 'resultLevel' on <defaultTerm> must be non negative integer.

3020705.Message:
The attribute 'qual:resultLevel' in <defaultTerm> must not be negative.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.4
3020705.ShortMessage: Attribute 'resultLevel' on <defaultTerm> must be non negative integer.

3020801.Message:
A <functionTerm> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <functionTerm> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.5

3020802.Message:
A <functionTerm> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <functionTerm>.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.5

3020803.Message:
A <functionTerm> object must have the required attributes 'qual:resultLevel'.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <functionTerm> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.5

3020804.Message:
A <functionTerm> object may contain exactly one MathML <math> element. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Qualitative Models namespace are permitted on a <functionTerm> object.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.5

3020805.Message:
The attribute 'qual:resultLevel' in <functionTerm> must be of the data type 'integer'.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.5
3020805.ShortMessage: Attribute 'resultLevel' on <functionTerm> must be non negative integer.

3020806.Message:
The attribute 'qual:resultLevel' in <functionTerm> must not be negative.
Reference: L3V1 Qual V1 Section 3.6.5
3020806.ShortMessage: Attribute 'resultLevel' on <functionTerm> must be non negative integer.

4010101.Message:
To conform to the Groups Package specification for SBML Level 3 Version 1, an SBML document must declare 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/groups/version1' as the XMLNamespace to use for elements of this package.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.1
4010101.ShortMessage: The Groups namespace is not correctly declared.

4010102.Message:
Wherever they appear in an SBML document, elements and attributes from the Groups Package must use the 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/groups/version1' namespace, declaring so either explicitly or implicitly.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.1

4010301.Message:
(Extends validation rule #10301 in the SBML Level 3 Core specification. TO DO list scope of ids)
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.3

4010302.Message:
The value of a 'groups:id' must conform to the syntax of the <sbml> data type 'SId'
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.3.1

4020101.Message:
In all SBML documents using the Groups Package, the <sbml> object must have the 'groups:required' attribute.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 4.1.2

4020102.Message:
The value of attribute 'groups:required' on the <sbml> object must be of data type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 4.1.2
4020102.ShortMessage: The groups:required attribute must be Boolean

4020103.Message:
The value of attribute 'groups:required' on the <sbml> object must be set to 'false'.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.1

4020201.Message:
A <model> object may contain one and only one instance of the <listOfGroups> element. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Groups namespaces are permitted on a <model> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.6

4020202.Message:
The <listOfGroups> subobject on a <model> object is optional, but if present, this container object must not be empty.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.6
4020202.ShortMessage: No Empty ListOf elements allowed on <Model>.

4020203.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotations subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfGroups> container object may only contain <group> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.6

4020204.Message:
A <listOfGroups> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <listOfGroups> object.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.6

4020301.Message:
A <group> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <group>.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 3.2

4020302.Message:
A <group> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <group>.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 3.2

4020303.Message:
A <group> object must have the required attribute 'groups:kind', and may have the optional attributes 'groups:id' and 'groups:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Groups namespaces are permitted on a <group> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.3

4020304.Message:
A <group> object may contain one and only one instance of the <listOfMembers> element. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Groups namespaces are permitted on a <group> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.3

4020305.Message:
The value of the attribute 'groups:kind' of a <group> object must conform to the syntax of SBML data type 'groupKind' and may only take on the allowed values of 'groupKind' defined in SBML; that is, the value must be one of the following: 'classification', 'partonomy' or 'collection'.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.3

4020306.Message:
The attribute 'groups:name' on a <group> must have a value of data type 'string'.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.3

4020307.Message:
The <listOfMembers> subobject on a <group> object is optional, but if present, this container object must not be empty.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.3
4020307.ShortMessage: No Empty ListOf elements allowed on <group>.

4020308.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotations subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfMembers> container object may only contain <member> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 3.2

4020309.Message:
A <listOfMembers> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <listOfMembers> object.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 3.2

4020310.Message:
A <listOfMembers> object may have the optional attributes 'groups:id' and 'groups:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Groups namespaces are permitted on a <listOfMembers> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.4

4020311.Message:
The attribute 'groups:name' on a <listOfMembers> must have a value of data type 'string'.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.4

4020312.Message:
If <listOfMembers> objects from different <group> objects contain <member> elements that reference the same SBase object, the 'sboTerm' attribute and any child <notes> or <annotation> elements set for those <listOfMembers> should be consistent, as they should all apply to the same referenced object.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.5.4

4020313.Message:
Member references may not be circular: no <member>'s 'idRef' or 'metaIdRef' may reference itself, its parent <listOfMembers>, nor its parent <group>. If a <member> references a <group> or a <listOfMembers>, the same restrictions apply to that subgroup's children: they may not reference the <member>, its parent <listOfMembers>, nor its parent <group>, and if any of those children reference a <group>, the same restrictions apply to them, etc.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.5.4

4020401.Message:
A <member> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <member>.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 3.2

4020402.Message:
A <member> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespaces are permitted on a <member>.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 3.2

4020403.Message:
A <member> object may have the optional attributes 'groups:id' and 'groups:name' and must have a value for one (and exactly one) of the attributes 'groups:idRef' and 'groups:metaIdRef'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Groups namespaces are permitted on a <member> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.5

4020404.Message:
The attribute 'groups:name' on a <member> must have a value of data type 'string'.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.5

4020405.Message:
The value of the attribute 'groups:idRef' of a <member> object must be the identifier of an existing object derived from the 'SBase' class and defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section
4020405.ShortMessage: The attribute 'idRef' must point to SBase object.

4020406.Message:
The value of the attribute 'groups:metaIdRef' of a <member> object must be the 'metaid' of an existing 'SBase' object defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.5
4020406.ShortMessage: The attribute 'metaIdRef' must point to SBase object.

4020407.Message:
The value of the attribute 'groups:idRef' of a <member> object must conform to the syntax of the SBML data type 'SId'.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.5

4020408.Message:
The value of the attribute 'groups:metaIdRef' of a <member> object must conform to the syntax of the SBML data type 'ID'.
Reference: L3V1 Groups V1 Section 3.5

6010101.Message:
To conform to Version 1 of the Layout package specification for SBML Level 3, an SBML document must declare the use of the following XML Namespace: 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/layout/version1'
Reference: L3V1 Layout V1 Section 3.1
6010101.ShortMessage: The layout ns is not correctly declared

6010102.Message:
Wherever they appear in an SBML document, elements and attributes from the Layout package must be declared either implicitly or explicitly to be in the XML namespace 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/layout/version1'
Reference: L3V1 Layout V1 Section 3.1

6010301.Message:
(Extends validation rule #10301 in the SBML Level 3 Version 1 Core specification.) Within a <model> object the values of the attributes id and layout:id on every instance of the following classes of objects must be unique across the set of all id and layout:id attribute values of all such objects in a model: the model itself, plus all contained <functionDefinition>, <compartment>, <species>, <reaction>, <speciesReference>, <modifierSpeciesReference>, <event>, and <parameter> objects, plus the <boundingBox>, <compartmentGlyph>, <generalGlyph>, <graphicalObject>, <layout>, <speciesGlyph>, <speciesReferenceGlyph>, <reactionGlyph>, <referenceGlyph> and <textGlyph> objects defined by the Layout package.
Reference: L3V1 Layout V1 Section 3.3

6010302.Message:
The value of the 'layout:id' attribute must conform to the SBML data type SId
Reference: L3V1 Layout V1 Section 3.3

6010401.Message:
